{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Such non-technical text data have been assembled into several corpora and have been made publicly available.",
    "Corpora such as Penn Treebank Corpus (Marcus et al., 1993), British National Corpus (BNC Consortium, 2007) and WikiText-2 (Merity et al., 2017) are used for the generic training of NLP models, and each of them contain tens of thousands, if not millions of words.",
    "Some corpora are designed for specific tasks.",
    "Amazon Customer Reviews (Bhatt et al., 2015) and IMDb Movie Reviews (Maas et al., 2011) are commonly used to train models for Sentiment Analysis.",
    "The Reuters Corpus (RCV1) (Rose et al., 2002) is routinely used for text clustering."
  ],
